    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1" facs="#f0001"/>
            <dateline>
                <hi rendition="#et">
                    <hi rendition="#k">London,</hi> Oct. 17.</hi>
            </dateline>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Extent and Population of America.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The following estimate of the extent, in<lb break="yes"/>square leagues, and population, of the con-<lb break="no"/>tinent of America in 1822, was lately trans-<lb break="no"/>mitted by Baron de Humboldt from Paris,<lb break="yes" />to President Bolivar, with the accompa-<lb break="no"/>nying Letter:</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell> <hi rendition="#i">Square Leagues.</hi></cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Population</hi></cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Mexico, or New Spain</cell>
                        <cell>75,830</cell>
                        <cell>6,800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Guatemala</cell>
                        <cell>16,740</cell>
                        <cell>1,600,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Cuba and Puerto Rico</cell>
                        <cell>4,430</cell>
                        <cell>800,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell rows="3">Colombia <list rendition="#leftBraced">
                            <item>Venezuela</item>
                            <item>N Granada</item>
                        </list></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><choice>
                                <sic>33,600</sic>
                                <corr type="editorial">33,700</corr>
                            </choice></cell>
                        <cell>900,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><choice>
                                <sic>58 ,50</sic>
                                <corr type="editorial">58,250</corr>
                            </choice></cell>
                        <cell><choice>
                                <sic>1,400,000</sic>
                                <corr type="editorial">1,800,000</corr>
                            </choice></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row><cell/></row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Peru</cell>
                        <cell><choice>
                                <sic>42  10</sic>
                                <corr type="editorial">42,150</corr>
                            </choice></cell>
                        <cell><choice>
                                <sic>1,800,000</sic>
                                <corr type="editorial">1,400,000</corr>
                            </choice></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Chili</cell>
                        <cell>14,240</cell>
                        <cell>1,100,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Buenos Ayres</cell>
                        <cell><choice>
                                <sic>1 6770</sic>
                                <corr type="editorial">126,770</corr>
                            </choice></cell>
                        <cell>2,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Total formerly Spanish</cell>
                        <cell>372,110</cell>
                        <cell>16,400,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   United States</cell>
                        <cell>125,440</cell>
                        <cell>10,200,000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>   Brazil</cell>
                        <cell>256,990</cell>
                        <cell>4,000,000</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                
                <p>The above surfaces have been calculat-<lb break="no"/>ed with great care, on maps
                    rectified by<lb break="yes"/>astronomical observations. The calcula-<lb
                        break="no"/>tions have been several times repeated by<lb break="yes"/>M.
                    Mathieu, member of the board of Lon-<lb break="no"/>gitude, and of the
                    Institute, as well as by<lb break="yes"/>myself. The results differ from
                        those<lb break="yes"/>published in 1809 in the Political Essays<lb
                        break="yes"/>on Mexico. Then the inhabited parts<lb break="yes"/>alone had
                    been calculated, without includ-<lb break="no"/>ing the desert regions, over
                    which the in-<lb break="no"/><pb n="[2]" facs="#f0002"/>dependent tribes of
                    indigenous inhabitants<lb break="yes"/>wander. Now the whole extent of each<lb
                        break="yes"/>country, to its furthest limits, has been<lb break="yes"
                    />measured.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The population of the different parts of<lb break="yes"/><choice>
                        <sic><hi rendition="#i">cidevant</hi></sic>
                        <corr type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">ci-devant</hi></corr>
                    </choice> Spanish America is very uncer-<lb break="no"/>tain; nevertheless each
                    portion has been<lb break="yes"/>calculated according to the latest data<lb
                        break="yes"/>which have reached me. The present es-<lb break="no"/>timate
                    ought to be considered in the same<lb break="yes"/>light, as all my other works
                    on America;<lb break="yes"/>they are no other than essays, in which<lb
                        break="yes"/>every thing will have to be done over<lb break="yes"/>again.
                    Statistical calculations can only<lb break="yes"/>be rendered perfect by
                    degrees, in like<lb break="yes"/>manner as the elements of meteorological<lb
                        break="yes"/>and astronomical tables</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Comparison</hi> &#x2014;Spain contains 16,094<lb break="yes"
                    />sq leagues; Europe contains 304 710 sq.<lb break="yes"/>leagues, and the whole
                    of Southern Amer-<lb break="no"/>ica, 581 891 sq leagues.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">(Signed) HUMBOLDT.</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
                <lb break="yes"/>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <lb break="yes"/>
        </body>
